properties.name: BEEKMAN 1802 HEIRLOOM VEGETABLE GARDEN
properties.description: Posted by Beekman1802 6725 State Route 10 Sharon Springs NY 13459When we bought the Beekman Mansion two years ago, our very first day found us pacing the grounds looking for the best location for an heirloom vegetable garden. The next day found us attacking the dirt with a rototiller. A few days later, Landreth Alaska Pea seeds were being pushed down into the still semi-frozen spring ground. The original owner of The Beekman Mansion, Judge William Beekman, ran a mercantile exchange across the street from his home. Given that Landreth Seeds was sending their seed catalogs to every home in America at that time, it’s a pretty safe bet that the brand of seeds Judge Beekman sold in his store was also Landreth. ￼ With the expert help of Landreth Seeds, we’ve planned out the 52 raised beds in the Heirloom Garden to reflect varieties that would have been planted during different periods of Beekman History: Early (1802-1850); Mid (1850 - 1900) and Modern (1900 - present.) The garden beds are constructed from local Hemlock, and stand 18 inches tall. Filled with organic soil, no chemical fertilizers or pesticides are ever added to the garden. Composted manure from The Farm at Beekman Mansion is the only additive. Beds are rotated every year, and planted with companion plantings to minimize weeding and other maintenance.
